			<div class="content" id="post-content-4396353">
									

<p>I felt like this went on for too long after the 'big moment' (although from my understanding this was part of the joke), which is why I downvoted. I probably would have upvoted if you somehow found a way to make the last line &quot;the steaks keep getting higher&quot;, because that was a great pun, but its impact was too diminished for me.</p>
<p>Additionally, there's something about the Apollyon classification which feels weird to me, which makes no sense because it plays perfectly into the article's pun. Maybe if you had an offset with the first page as Euclid/Keter and just a description of some of the earlier events, and then a new revision with the Apollyon class and the logs? I'm not sure if that would help though :x</p>

